title: ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'deeplabcut.pose_estimation_tensorflow.lib'
body:
**Describe the bug**

I pulled the latest code and tried reinstalling and got a bug stating a missing module was not present installed. I'm running Ubuntu 18.04 and the code was running fine before the pull this morning.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior, i.e.:
1. Pull the latest code (git pull from /dlc directory...)
2. Either run ./reinstall.sh script or "python setup.py install"

**Expected behavior**
Importing deeplabcut shouldn't throw errors.

**Desktop (please complete the following information about your system):**
 - OS: Ubuntu 18.04
 - DeepLabCut Version latest version (can't check the version as it can't be imported).
